SUMMARY:Edna's Haven
DESCRIPTION:Edna’s Haven is a resource center that provides information and referrals\, resources and linkages\, case management\, financial assistance\, a charging station and computer access\, coffee and snacks and more to those experiencing homelessness. \nPeer-Recovery Counseling\, health screenings\, veteran’s services and job fairs are also available at times throughout the year as well as soup kitchen services and a food pantry. Edna’s Haven can also be used for mail access for people that do not have a place to receive their mail. \n\nContact Edna’s Haven at EdnasHaven@mhainspire.org. \nThis program is supported in part by the Morris County Commissioners. \n  \nSoup Kitchen\n11:30 AM to 12:30 PM\, Monday through Friday.\nA food pantry is also available on site. \nSchedule of events\nMondays- Music\nTuesdays- Pizza Day\nWednesday- Bingo\nThursday- Peer-Recovery Counseling\nFriday- Movies \n 
URL:https://www.mhainspire.org/event/ednas-haven/2026-03-16/
LOCATION:Trinity Lutheran Church\, 123 E. Blackwell Street\, Dover\, NJ\, 07801\, United States
CATEGORIES:Community Programs
END:VEVENT
